<h2>Red, Green, and Yellow</h2>

<ol>
  <li>6 omz firm red tomatoes,peeled</li>
  <li>1/2 large cucumber,unpeeled</li>
  <li>4 eggs</li>
   <li>1 tso salt</li>
  <li>1 scallion, chopped</li>
  <li>1/2 cup vegetable oil</li>
  <li>2 tsp rice win</li>
  <li>A few drops of sesame oil</li>
  
  
  

  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  <h2>How to prepare it step by step.</h2>
 
<ol>
  <li> Cut the tomatoes in half crosswise, then cut across into wedges. Cut the cucumber in half lengthwise, then slice crosswise. Put the eggs in a bowl and beat with a pinch of salt and a few pieces of scallion</li>
  
  
  
  
  <li> Heat about half the oil in a preheated wok, add the eggs, and lightly scramble them until set, but not too dry. Remove and keep warm. Heat the remaining oil in the wok.</li>
  
  
  
  
  
  <li> Add the vegetables and remaining scallion and stir-fry for 1 minute. Add the remaining salt, and stir-fry for another minute. Blend in the eggs and race wine. sprinkle with the sesame oil, and serve hot.


<ol>
</body>
</html>

